  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nThis bug was surfaced by @DavidHaller in Optimism's Discord.\r\n\r\n**NOTE: David Haller uses a Windows OS when he receives this error.** \r\n\r\nWhen trying to deploy a simple `Greeter` contract (Hardhat's default contract template) fails when using Hardhat's default script, under `./scripts/`, to deploy it.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Git clone repo: `git clone https://github.com/DavidHaller43/optimism_Greeter.git`\r\n2. npx hardhat compile --network optimism\r\n3. npx hardhat run ./scripts/sample-script.js --network optimism\r\n4. See the following error:\r\n```\r\nError: cannot estimate gas; transaction may fail or may require manual gas limit (error={\"name\":\"ProviderError\",\"code\":-32000,\"_isProviderError\":true}, method=\"estimateGas\", transaction=...})\r\n\r\nreason: 'cannot estimate gas; transaction may fail or may require manual gas limit', code: 'UNPREDICTABLE_GAS_LIMIT', error: ProviderError: execution reverted: Contract creation code contains unsafe opcodes. Did you use the right compiler or pass an unsafe constructor argument? at HttpProvider.request\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nSince the above repro steps succeed when on Mac and Linux, the expected behavior is that it should succeed on Windows just like on Mac and Linux -- that is, the contract should deploy and return the address on the console.\r\n\r\n**System Specs:**\r\n - OS: Windows\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nThis came issue was surfaced from a user on Discord.\r\nLinks to the original issue:\r\nhttps://discord.com/channels/667044843901681675/676980316518481930/871492543056052254\r\n",
